    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "ab39ec08_39883626",
        "filename": "milo/common/model/pool.go",
        "patchSetId": 5
      },
      "lineNbr": 48,
      "author": {
        "id": 1002080
      },
      "writtenOn": "2018-04-12T20:58:09Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "The reason was because I really wanted a \"short\" name.  I think I can partially justify it by saying the Swarming hostname is an \"implicit\" dimension - It is the host that the bot is connected to.\n\nBut then dimensions would be used in two different ways in Milo, so I agree that\u0027s problematic.  I\u0027ll use \"PoolDescriptor\" Maybe? Avoiding \"Definition\" since it\u0027s isn\u0027t as much defined in Milo as inferred.",
      "parentUuid": "3609ff61_c0d50ad3",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 47,
        "startChar": 1,
        "endLine": 48,
        "endChar": 12
      },
      "revId": "72ba4bf3a50741fbfd5fc873fb70b8ff4a37aad3",
