    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "00565c10_a252dd3c",
        "filename": "milo/common/model/pool.go",
        "patchSetId": 5
      },
      "lineNbr": 52,
      "author": {
        "id": 1114299
      },
      "writtenOn": "2018-04-12T20:35:18Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "dimensions the struct or dimensions the field? this is ambiguous\n\nanyway, I think it would be better to have method instead of a field. \nThe field value gets stale as soon as one modifies Host or Dimensions field, and one cannot recompute it without recreating the whole thing. No such problem with a method.\nWhoever needs to store the sha1, can compute it using the method and store along with this struct.",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 52,
        "startChar": 63,
        "endLine": 52,
        "endChar": 73
      },
      "revId": "72ba4bf3a50741fbfd5fc873fb70b8ff4a37aad3",
      "serverId": "3ce6091f-6c88-37e8-8c75-72f92ae8dfba",
      "unresolved": true
    },
    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "42d09583_337ad63c",
        "filename": "milo/common/model/pool.go",
        "patchSetId": 5
      },
      "lineNbr": 52,
      "author": {
        "id": 1002080
      },
      "writtenOn": "2018-04-12T20:58:09Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "Field was used to avoid more complexity and unnecessary computation (Basically as a \"free\" cache).  As long as the callers are cooperative (Don\u0027t modify dimensions without fixing Hash), it\u0027s cheaper this way.  Besides, I think by splitting this out into a separate entity, the hash will need to be the key anyways.  I think I\u0027d like to keep the pre-computation of the SHA1, and document that these are supposed to be immutable.\n\nMaking these fields private with accessors won\u0027t work with Datastore either without some crazy PLS magic, so I\u0027d want to avoid that.",
      "parentUuid": "00565c10_a252dd3c",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 52,
        "startChar": 63,
        "endLine": 52,
        "endChar": 73
      },
      "revId": "72ba4bf3a50741fbfd5fc873fb70b8ff4a37aad3",
      "serverId": "3ce6091f-6c88-37e8-8c75-72f92ae8dfba",
      "unresolved": true
    },
